This press briefing by Press Secretary Jay Carney discusses the meeting between President Obama and congressional leaders to discuss the budget and avoid a government shutdown. Carney says that the meeting was productive and that progress is being made towards finding a deal. He emphasizes the importance of reaching a compromise and expresses the President's willingness to work nonstop until a deal is reached. Carney also addresses questions about the possibility of a government shutdown, the impact it would have on the American people, and the number of federal employees that would be furloughed. He also discusses the President's views on the national debt as a threat to national security and the need for long-term deficit reduction. Carney mentions the President's disagreement with the Republican budget proposal put forth by Congressman Ryan and highlights the President's commitment to a balanced approach to deficit reduction.